“the  dissolved  Kumpulan  Wang”  means  the  Kumpulan  Wang 
simpanan Guru which was established under the repealed Education 
Act  1961  [Act  43/1961];

“teacher  professionalism  development”  means  any  course  or 
training  provided  to  enhance  the  quality  and  competency  of  a 
teacher;

(a)  to  assist  the  Ministry  responsible  for  education  in 
organizing  activities  related  to  teacher  professionalism 
development;

(d)  to grant loans, financing and scholarships to a teacher or 
the  teacher’s  child  in  accordance  with  the  procedures 
as  may  be  determined  by  the  Yayasan;

(d)  an Education service Officer who is serving at the Ministry 
responsible for education who shall be appointed by the 
Minister;

(iii)  any other offence punishable with imprisonment, 
whether in itself only or in addition to or in lieu 
of  a  fine,  for  more  than  three  months;

(c)  if his conduct, whether in connection with his duties as 
a  member  of  the  Board  or  otherwise,  has  been  such  as 
to  bring  discredit  to  the  Yayasan;

(b)  all  or  any  part  of  the  charges  imposed  by  or  payable  to 
the Yayasan under this Act or any subsidiary legislation 
made  under  this  Act;

(e)  all moneys and property which may in any manner become 
payable  to  or  vested  in  the  Yayasan  in  respect  of  any 
matter  incidental  to  its  functions  and  powers;
